      "comment" : "Avalanches can be triggered by one single winter sports enthusiast. Danger zones occur on steep slopes in all aspects, behind drops in the landscape. Particularly on very steep shady slopes above 1800m, avalanches can fracture down to deeper-down layers inside the snowpack and then grow to large size.  Whumpf noises and fractures which appear when treading upon the snowpack are alarm signals. At low and intermediate altitudes, medium-sized wet loose-snow avalanches can be expected in very steep terrain. On steep grass-covered slopes, glide-snow avalanches can occur. Zones with glide cracks should under all circumstances be avoided."
